#ROOM
Vnum     26500
Name     &OThe Southfury River - West Bank&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     You stand on the western bank of the Southfury River. The red, rocky
terrain of Durotar lies just across the rushing water to the east. The
vast, golden savannah of the Barrens stretches out before you to the west,
heat shimmering off the dry earth.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    25022
Desc      Across the river to Razor Hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26501
Desc      Further into the Barrens.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26501
Name     &OThe Far Watch Post&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A small Horde outpost stands here, guarding the crossing from Durotar.
Spiked wooden barricades and a few lean-tos provide meager shelter for
the guards stationed here. The Gold Road begins just to the west.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26500
Desc      The river bank.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26502
Desc      The Gold Road.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26509 2 26501
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26502
Name     &OThe Gold Road - Northern Junction&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     You are standing on the Gold Road, a well-traveled dirt path that bisects
the Barrens from north to south. To the north, the road leads toward the
forests of Ashenvale. To the south, it continues toward the Crossroads.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26528
Desc      Toward Ashenvale.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26503
Desc      Toward the Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26501
Desc      The Far Watch Post.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26500 3 26502
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26503
Name     &OThe Gold Road - North&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The Gold Road stretches endlessly in both directions. The air is dry and
tastes of dust. Stunted trees and tall, yellowed grass line the path,
providing perfect cover for the predators of the plains.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26502
Desc      Northern Junction.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26504
Desc      Approaching the Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26503 2 26503
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26504
Name     &OThe Crossroads - Northern Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A large, spiked watchtower looms over the road here. The sound of bustling
activity and the smell of roasting meat drift from the south. This is the
heart of the Barrens, where all paths eventually meet.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26503
Desc      The Gold Road.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26505
Desc      The Crossroads center.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26509 1 26504
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26505
Name     &OThe Crossroads - Center&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The Crossroads is a chaotic hub of Horde activity. Orcs, Trolls, and Tauren
mingle here, preparing for hunts or resting between travels. A massive
bonfire burns in the center of the square, surrounded by basic supply huts.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26504
Desc      The north gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26510
Desc      The south gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26514
Desc      Toward Ratchet.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26506
Desc      Toward the Oases.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26510 1 26505
Reset O 0 26508 1 26505
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26506
Name     &OPath to the Forgotten Pools&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A narrow trail winds west away from the Crossroads. The dry grass gives
way to strange, vibrant flora as you approach a hidden source of water.
The air feels slightly more humid here.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26505
Desc      The Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26507
Desc      The Forgotten Pools.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26502 2 26506
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26507
Name     &CThe Forgotten Pools&d~
Sector   water_swim~
Desc     A lush oasis sits nestled in a natural depression. Crystal clear water
bubbles up from the earth, feeding a variety of plants that shouldn't
exist in this climate. Strange fissures in the ground glow with a faint,
unnatural light.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26506
Desc      The path back.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26508
Desc      Grol'dom Farm.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26505 3 26507
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26508
Name     &OThe Grol'dom Farm&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A small, struggling farmstead has been carved out of the savannah. A few
huts stand near a small field of dry crops. The area is plagued by
constant raids from the nearby quilboar tribes.
~
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26507
Desc      The Forgotten Pools.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26509
Desc      Thorn Hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26509
Name     &OThorn Hill&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The terrain rises sharply here, dominated by massive, razor-sharp thorns
that erupt from the earth like giant claws. This is the edge of quilboar
territory, and the grunts of the beast-men echo through the ravines.
~
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26508
Desc      Grol'dom Farm.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26507 4 26509
Reset O 0 26504 2 26509
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26510
Name     &OThe Gold Road - South of Crossroads&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     South of the Crossroads, the Gold Road continues its steady path through
the heart of the Barrens. To the west, you can see the shimmering heat
waves rising from the Stagnant Oasis.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26505
Desc      The Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26512
Desc      Further south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26511
Desc      The Stagnant Oasis.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26504 2 26510
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26511
Name     &CThe Stagnant Oasis&d~
Sector   water_swim~
Desc     Unlike the Forgotten Pools, this oasis is choked with thick reeds and
murky water. A massive, shell-like mountain rises from the center of the
pool, claimed by a powerful tribe of Kolkar centaur.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26510
Desc      The Gold Road.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26501 3 26511
Reset M 0 26514 1 26511
Reset O 0 26513 1 26511
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26512
Name     &OThe Gold Road - Southern Junction&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The road splits here. To the south, the path leads toward Camp Taurajo
and the Great Lift. To the west, a rugged trail winds through the hills
toward the entrance of Mulgore.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26510
Desc      Toward Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26521
Desc      Toward Camp Taurajo.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26513
Desc      The road to Mulgore.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26503 2 26512
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26513
Name     &OThe Road to Mulgore&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The path climbs steadily into the foothills of the western mountains.
A massive wooden gate, the Red Rocks, marks the boundary between the
savannah and the ancestral lands of the Tauren.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26512
Desc      The Gold Road.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    25500
Desc      Into Mulgore.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26514
Name     &OThe Road to Ratchet&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     This well-worn path leads east from the Crossroads toward the coast.
Trade caravans frequently travel this route, bringing supplies from the
neutral port of Ratchet to the Horde interior.
~
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26505
Desc      The Crossroads.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26515
Desc      Toward the coast.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26500 2 26514
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26515
Name     &OThe Merchant Coast - Overlook&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     From this vantage point, you can see the Great Sea stretching out to the
eastern horizon. Below, the bustling goblin port of Ratchet is visible,
its mechanical cranes and wooden docks humming with activity.
~
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26514
Desc      The road back.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction down~
ToRoom    26516
Desc      Down into Ratchet.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26516
Name     &xRatchet - Main Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Ratchet is a marvel of goblin engineering and greed. The smell of oil,
saltwater, and exotic spices fills the air. Steam-powered machines hiss
in the background as merchants of all races haggle over goods.
~
Exit
Direction up~
ToRoom    26515
Desc      The overlook.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    26517
Desc      The docks.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26519
Desc      The South Road.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26511 1 26516
Reset M 0 26512 2 26516
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26517
Name     &xRatchet - The Docks&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A massive wooden pier extends into the bay. Large merchant ships are
moored here, being loaded and unloaded by frantic peons and mechanical
lifts. A large boat with a shark-head prow is currently docked.
~
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    26516
Desc      Ratchet Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    26518
Desc      North Merchant Coast.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26512 1 26517
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26518
Name     &OThe North Merchant Coast&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The sandy beach stretches north away from Ratchet. The wrecks of several
ships lie rotting in the surf, casualties of the treacherous reefs or
pirate raids.
~
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    26517
Desc      Ratchet Docks.
~
